    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nhttps://code.visualstudio.com/api/references/vscode-api#ProgressLocation\n\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt probably makes sense to add:\n\n- a `location` field (list of desired locations) which hints to the presenter how/where to display. \n- `cancellable` flag which decides if a cancel button (or right-click menu) should be shown by the presenter\n\nTo make Progress messages cancellable, ~~one approach is to add a `ProgressCancel` event. It can be executed with msg-id to cancel a given Progress message.~~ `nvim_echo({id=..., status='cancel')` already should work.",
